descp2: One of `"valid"`, `"causal"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).`"causal"` results in causal (dilated) convolutions, e.g. output[t] does not depend on input[t+1:]. Useful when modeling temporal data where the model should not violate the temporal order. See WaveNet: A Generative Model for Raw Audio, section 2.1.
